Dear Solmee, I know it's a personal choice to get cosmetic procedures done, and the kind that you get are minor compared to some others. But I wish you could accept that you are beautiful without those. When you are so young, you don't need to constantly get procedures. I know in Seoul, everyone does it ... and beauty standards are kind of toxic to young people's minds. I'm just afraid at the rate you get them and how you justify it may keep pushing you to get more and more as you get older. I was overweight until I became 30 years old and then through exercise and diet got healthier. So I know your struggles. I still struggle with it and it's challenging not to succumb to easy methods. Your face is unique and your personality is what really shines through.
